<procedure xmlns:dc="http://www.purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.s1000d.org/S1000D_6/xml_schema_flat/proced.xsd">
  <title>Bicycle Pre-Ride Check - Crew Procedure</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>This document outlines the crew procedure for a pre-ride bicycle check, ensuring rider safety and optimal performance. It details the steps for inspecting critical components and performing necessary adjustments.</p>
  </introduction>
  <step>
    <step_title>Crew Procedure Steps</step_title>
    <step_item>
      <step_item_title>1. Brakes</step_item_title>
      <step_item_list>
        <step_item_list_item>Inspect brake pads for wear.</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item>Ensure brake levers operate smoothly.</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item>Verify cable integrity (no cuts or fraying).</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item>Confirm proper brake function - both front and rear.</step_item_list_item>
      </step_item_list>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <step_item_title>2. Tires</step_item_title>
      <step_item_list>
        <step_item_list_item>Tire pressure (see table below for recommended ranges).</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item>Inspect tires for cracks, splits, or embedded objects.</step_item_list_item>
      </step_item_list>
      <table_data>
        <header_row>
          <header>Header</header>
          <header>Terrain</header>
          <header>Minimum Pressure</header>
          <header>Maximum Pressure</header>
        </header_row>
        <data_row>
          <data>Row</data>
          <data>Off Road</data>
          <data>35 lbs</data>
          <data>40 lbs</data>
        </data_row>
        <data_row>
          <data>Row</data>
          <data>On Road</data>
          <data>55 lbs</data>
          <data>60 lbs</data>
        </data_row>
      </table_data>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <step_item_title>3. Wheels</step_item_title>
      <step_item_list>
        <step_item_list_item>Spin wheels to verify smooth rotation.</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item>Listen for unusual noises indicating bearing issues.</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item>Inspect spokes for breakage.</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item>Ensure spokes are tight.</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item>Confirm axle nuts are securely tightened.</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item>Confirm wheel is 'true' (not wobbling).</step_item_list_item>
      </step_item_list>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <step_item_title>4. Headset</step_item_title>
      <step_item_list>
        <step_item_list_item>Ensure headset bearings are tight and smooth.</step_item_list_item>
      </step_item_list>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <step_item_title>5. Chain</step_item_title>
      <step_item_list>
        <step_item_list_item>Verify easy movement of chain links.</step_item_list_item>
      </step_item_list>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <step_item_title>6. Handlebar &amp; Stem</step_item_title>
      <p>Do <em>not</em> ride with a cracked stem.</p>
      <step_item_list>
        <step_item_list_item><strong>Stem Cracked:</strong> Replace stem immediately.</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item><strong>Stem Loose:</strong> Tighten stem.</step_item_list_item>
        <step_item_list_item><strong>Handlebars Twist:</strong> Tighten clamp bolt.</step_item_list_item>
      </step_item_list>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <step_item_title>7. Computer Display</step_item_title>
      <p>Ensure the computer is displaying accurate information (example):</p>
      <table_data>
        <header_row>
          <header>Header</header>
          <header>Component</header>
          <header>Displayed Value</header>
        </header_row>
        <data_row>
          <data>Row</data>
          <data>Speed</data>
          <data>0 mph</data>
        </data_row>
        <data_row>
          <data>Row</data>
          <data>Distance</data>
          <data>0 miles</data>
        </data_row>
      </table_data>
    </step_item>
  </step>
  <notes>
    <p>This procedure is a guideline; adapt it based on specific bicycle types and rider needs.</p>
    <p>Regular maintenance and inspection are crucial for safety and performance.</p>
    <p>Always prioritize safety; if unsure about any component, seek professional assistance.</p>
  </notes>
</procedure>